Reference

All functions

covid_us_states

Provides the Dataset for the Confirmed Covid-19 Cases and Deaths by States in the U.S, reported by The New York Times.

create_datatable()

Creates a list of 2 elements relating to the spatial data of Covid-19 testing in the U.S

create_map_data()

Creates a list of 2 elements relating to the spatial data of Covid-19 cases in the U.S

custome_theme()

Custom theme for maps and bar charts

error_msg()

Creates error message if Shiny App input is empty

launch_app()

Load Shiny Application from inst/app directory

tests_raw

Reported Covid-19 Testing Data across all U.S States from 2020-01-22 to 2020-10-07

ui_input()

Creates reactive input for Shiny app

us_pop_ests

Provides the dataset for the estimated population by U.S county, primarily used for relational joins.

us_states_map

Raw US map data for states
